  <bioghist id="aspace_f02706f6b74d55e37cfa87e3ee031e2d">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Francis M. Kelley was born in Phelps, New York, in 1895. He was a graduate of the New York State College of Veterinary Medicine, Class of 1918. After graduation he opened a practice in Mount Morris, New York, which he maintained until his retirement in 1968. He died in 1982</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_ed96a72afde290a1404f8cefbe37c853">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, class notes, ephemera, and other papers from Kelley's education at Cornell University and his veterinary career in Mount Morris, New York.</p>  </scopecontent>
